speech.p: I have run out of time, but I would say in conclusion that the PCC and the press will have heard hon. Members’ remarks in the debate. The Chairman of the Culture, Media and Sport Committee will be aware that the PCC is conducting its own review following the phone hacking allegations. As well as being a criminal offence, phone hacking is of course a breach of the code. The PCC is reviewing the matter to see whether it can make its recommendations stronger, but it will have heard the important—
House adjourned without Question put (Standing Order No. 9(7)).
Official Report, 26 April 2011: in Division 257, column 144, in the Noes insert: “Shannon, Jim”
